"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-golf-1932076-Tom-Kim-Olympics-golf-military-service\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Tom Kim has explained why he broke down in tears after missing out on a medal at the2024 Olympicsgolf tournament, insisting it had nothing to do with his future military service.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6, \"end\": 9, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.8773982902203962, \"rank\": 0.1370596278225386, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The South Korean golfer had put himself in the driving seat to land a bronze medal for most of the final day at Le Golf National before wrecking his chances on the final hole.\", \"from\": 182, \"to\": 357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 192, \"end\": 198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9969225370946855, \"rank\": 0.0030557121600796027, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He played a double-bogey on the 18th, which saw him tumble down the order, and he eventually finished eighth on the leaderboard.\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USA's Scottie Scheffler took the gold on -19, with Team GB's Tommy Fleetwood a shot adrift to claim the silver medal and Hideki Matsuyama beating Kim to bronze for Japan.\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 489, \"end\": 492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.933875487425313, \"rank\": 0.06989313043858002, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 495, \"end\": 512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scottie Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}, {\"begin\": 540, \"end\": 547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9538924725698925, \"rank\": 0.04833548029614076, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 550, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommy Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\"}, {\"begin\": 610, \"end\": 626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hideki Matsuyama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\"}, {\"begin\": 635, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.8773982902203962, \"rank\": 0.1370596278225386, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9997130644441432, \"rank\": 0.0002775885203063133, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old would have been able to avoid carrying out his compulsory military service in South Korea if he had won a medal at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9742824280062664, \"rank\": 0.014715550175038455, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Kim insisted that it wasn't on his mind after his disappointing finish - and admitted he was \\\"surprised\\\" to be overwhelmed by his emotions after missing out on a medal.\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 811, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.8773982902203962, \"rank\": 0.1370596278225386, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery+is the new home of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The streamer is set to broadcast 3,800 hours of sport live from Paris.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1090, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999995012331, \"rank\": 4.98780749642992e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports fans can getDiscovery+ for \\u00a33.99a month until the end of 2024 via Amazon Prime's video channels.\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1171, \"end\": 1183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"score\": 0.9991042782412565, \"rank\": 0.0008965247247050184, \"text\": \"Amazon Prime\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This also comes with anAmazon Prime 30-day free trial.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When asked if military service had triggered his tears at the finish, Kim replied: \\\"Not at all.\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.8773982902203962, \"rank\": 0.1370596278225386, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I wasn't really thinking about that at all.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was just trying to get a medal for my country and not myself.\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1461, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have never been really this emotional after a round.\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These emotions are surprising but I think it's just all the hard work I have done this year to put myself in this position - those things are coming out.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And just the things Scottie [Scheffler] said to me after the round really kind of came out and I am just trying to hold it together.\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.226509126306109e-28, \"text\": \"Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's a really good buddy of mine and understands what I have gone through.\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just those things and a friend to say something like that after what he did [winning the gold], it means a lot.\\\"\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rules in his native country state that he can steer clear of the military if he gains a medal at the Olympics or a gold at the Asian Games.\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His triumph has to occur while representing his country, so even winning a major on the PGA Tour would not be enough.\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2227, \"end\": 2235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PGA_Tour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6491502601324507e-14, \"text\": \"PGA Tour\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PGA_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PGA_Tour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kim does have two more opportunities to dodge his military stint in South Korea, which can last between 18 and 21 months.\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.8773982902203962, \"rank\": 0.1370596278225386, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9742824280062664, \"rank\": 0.014715550175038455, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is mandatory for all men over the age of 18 to serve in the army before they pass the cut-off of 28.\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2594, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  He can still win gold at the Asian Games in 2026 in Nagoya, while the next Olympics will be hosted in Los Angeles in 2028.\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nagoya\", \"score\": 0.9999991017047647, \"rank\": 8.981720816826724e-07, \"text\": \"Nagoya\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nagoya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nagoya\"}, {\"begin\": 2831, \"end\": 2842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999988044692, \"rank\": 1.1336066225158076e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kim will still be young enough to compete in those tournaments, which may explain why he was not upset.\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2852, \"end\": 2855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.8773982902203962, \"rank\": 0.1370596278225386, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashi